manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: EKEN Smart Wireless Doorbell Camera for Home Security
Features of EKEN Wireless Doorbell Camera

High-Definition Wide-Angle Len Capture crystal-clear footage with a wide-angle lens, offering real-time live view or recorded videos with sharp details. Secure Cloud Storage Solution Enjoy AES-128 encrypted cloud storage with an optional subscription plan (sold separately). Explore a 30-day free-trial for seamless recording, reviewing, and sharing of your videos.

Share with friends and family The owner account can share to 8 other accounts. Up to 3 users may view the video feed at one time, and only 1 user can use the intercom at one time. Smart AI Human Detection Enable the AI human detection function to accurately identify people and ignore other moving objects like cars and trees. Chime Included Place the doorbell chime in your dining room, kitchen, or courtyard to hear when someone rings your doorbell. Weather-Resistant IP65 dustproof and waterproof certification ensures the video doorbell can withstand rain, sun, heat, or chill, providing reliable security all year.

Is the doorbell camera compatible with 5GHz Wi-Fi networks? This doorbell camera only works with 2.4G Wi-Fi. You'll need to have separate networks for 2.4GHz and 5GHz Wi-Fi. Make sure they have different names, and connect the camera to the 2.4GHz network. Do I need to buy an SD memory card for this doorbell camera? This doorbell camera doesn't use SD cards; it stores videos in the cloud. Can I install the doorbell camera easily? Yes, it's easy. The user manual has all the steps. How many users can view the doorbell camera at the same time? The main account can allow access to the device for 8 other accounts. While 3 users can watch the video simultaneously, only one can use the intercom at a time. Can this doorbell camera withstand weather or is it waterproof? No, this doorbell camera isn't waterproof, though it is weatherproof. It comes with an IP65 rating, it can withstand different weather conditions, including protection from dust and light water spray, ideal for various climates.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2023
reviews.reviewText: So, I bought two of these bad boys for our apartment since we have a front and back door to our unit. For the price, you can’t beat the quality and functionality! My only complaint would be the battery life, but based on how well this item works for the price-point, I can see why the battery life is lacking. The motion sensor is very active, even on low, which is a good thing because that means it’s doing it’s job to alert you. I set the proximity range to low, and the humanoid detection mode to high, which supposedly drops recording sensitivity down until the unit is confident that there’s an actual person within range vs an animal, or another object. So far, the unit has used anywhere from 7-10% battery per day, depending on the activity level at my complex. Do the math and that’s somewhere between 10-14 days of usage on a full charge. You might say that’s not too shabby, which it isn’t, but considering that it takes nearly that long to charge back up when it’s fully drained, it’s worth pointing out. My only other issue is more of a suggestion for the manufacturer, and that is, please make a model with an SD card option so the user subscription is optional. I’d rather pay more upfront and have the ability to record and erase my own data vs putting it on a cloud network. Video/ Picture quality is pretty darn good, especially at night in low-light environments. Overall, I’m happy with the purchase and would buy it again. I’d also recommend this item to anybody looking for an entry-level, budget-friendly doorbell security cam. The product comes with simple directions, is easy to install, and has some nice features, such as: night vision, screenshot, landscape view and 2-way intercom. I like that they provide you screws and double sided tape for the mounting housing too. This gives the user a means to secure the housing two ways, depending on what’s best for your particular application. You can even use both if you really want to secure it down. I also like that you can easily share access with family members by email invite or QR code. If you’re in the market for some added security, looking to enhance to your outdated doorbell, or simply would like to put a face to the visitor, then look no further! This blows a lot of other higher priced competitors out of the water, the reviews speak for themselves.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Great product for the price. The app is quick to alert and the chime is loud enough to hear throughout the house. Camera is good quality and catches everything very clearly. Easy to use and easy app install. Would recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great and useful
reviews.reviewText: The doorbell with video camera is perfect for what I need it for. I can see what is going on in my porch or drive way. In my area there has been someone breaking into cars and stealing things off our porches. This really helps me to make sure that my car and property is ok and has a motion detection feature that will help me to catch the person who has been causing this problem. It really is great and useful for those who have a disability or even a hard time getting up to check who is at the door. You can simply check through the app on your phone or tablet to see who is there without getting up. I'm really thankful for this item. It has really helped me so much.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Clear recordings with crisp audio sound.
reviews.reviewText: This is an amazing camera. We have been using this camera for a business office for several months now with no issues. Signal is great and I love the quality of video and sound recording.The battery charge lasts several days with high volume usage. Only need to charge it on the weekends when the office is closed. The system also notifies you via app or website when there is activity at the door or when the battery is running low.I work at multiple offices, so being able to check my camera even when I am across town is extremally helpful. I am also able to tune into the mic when a client is at my door, to answer their questions or provide them a time of when I will be returning. This is a definite must have for any home owner or business. And with this price, you cant get a better deal.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Needs A Lot of Improvement *UPDATE*
reviews.reviewText: The video quality on this is good however, it’s not really worth the money.Immediately after I charge it to 100% it will randomly drop down to 75% within 30 minutes. It will then stay around 70% and go up and down on its own without me charging it.It does not capture everything. I live in an apartment, and my neighbors door is next to mine. It’s like a 90 degree angle, so I can see their door completely through the camera. The camera will sometimes record them going to their door, and other times it doesn’t capture them at all. Even though it’s is literally right in front of the camera. Makes me worried that someone could easily sneak up to my door without the camera ever catching them.Any time it sends an alert that someone is at the door, they are already gone by the time I get it. This camera only captures people right before they go out of frame. Pretty much defeats the purpose.*UPDATE*Customer service reached out to me after my review. They gave me a full refund since I was having issues, which was nice.The battery of the camera seems to have mostly fixed itself. It no longer drops down to 70% after charging, it stays charged for the most part now.It does still have issues with catching things in the frame on time, but it does notify me if someone is at my door.Also, they have a 30 day free trial for the cloud storage so that’s nice.Overall this camera isn’t too bad if your on a budget.
